#. 2: sound
#. 3: sound
msgctxt "Talk_100"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Hey, check it out. I'm practicing my\n"
"singing! \n"
"\n"
"<2.so>You know, if you didn't go to Kheel,\n"
"I never would have realized how much I\n"
"actually like to sing.\n"
"<3.so>But thanks to you, I'm having a blast!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_101"
msgid ""
"<1.so>I love singing here! Only the mountains\n"
"are listening!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_110"
msgid "<1.so>I'm going to go sing at the village shrine!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_111"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The elder said he likes the way I sing!\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I'm gonna go eat some <2.se_co>salmon meunière<3.re_co>\n"
"and practice some more tomorrow!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (red)
#. 3: reset_colour
#. 4: sound2
msgctxt "Talk_200"
msgid ""
"<1.so>Oh, hey! I've been practicing with my\n"
"dad!\n"
"\n"
"When I told him about the <2.se_co>Warbler's Nest<3.re_co>\n"
"shrine, he told me about the history of\n"
"the ancient shrines!\n"
"I wonder how many shrines there are in\n"
"the world. Do you think you can find\n"
"them all?\n"
"How about this? <4.so>If you find all of them,\n"
"I'll give you something special!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_201"
msgid ""
"<1.so>So I guess there are lots of shrines out\n"
"there! If you find all of them, I'll\n"
"congratulate you!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
msgctxt "Talk_210"
msgid ""
"<1.so>On my way to go practice at the village\n"
"shrine!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: sound
#. 2: set_colour (blue)
#. 3: reset_colour
msgctxt "Talk_220"
msgid ""
"<1.so>The elder said he likes the way I sing!\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"I'm gonna go eat some <2.se_co>salmon meunière<3.re_co>.\n"
"I can practice more tomorrow!"
msgstr ""

